              ]
            }
          ],
          "REFERENCE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "code": "J,JP/G,7,53,198101",
                "code_unit": [
                  {
                    "unit": "J,JP/G,7,53,198101",
                    "doi": "10.1088/0305-4616/7/1/010",
                    "field": {
                      "reference_type": "J",
                      "reference": {
                        "code": "JP/G",
                        "number": null,
                        "volume": "7",
                        "part": null,
                        "issue": null,
                        "page": "53"
                      },
                      "date": 198101
                    }
                  }
                ],
                "unit_combination": "(%)"
              },
              "free_text": [
                ""
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "p-wave neutron strength functions have been extracted",
                " from the average radiative capture cross-sections at",
                " 24 KeV, using the latest available values of average",
                " radiation-width, level-spacing, strength functions",
                " for s-wave, and those (except strength function) for",
                " p-wave"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ANALYSIS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Recently Weigmann et al., Phys.Rev.C20(1979)115, have",
                " pointed out that a short-range energy dependence of",
                " strength function is not uncommon. Therefore, it is",
                " desirable to extract p-wave strength functions from",
                " average capture cross sections using actual p-wave",
                " resonance parameters.",
                "For an expression for the average capture cross",
                " sections as a sum of partial cross-sections for",
                " different angular momenta of the incident neutrons,",
                " formula by Bilpuch et al.,Ann.Phys.10(1960)455, was",
                " used.",
                "Assumption that only s- and p-wave neutrons contribute",
                " to the sigma(n,g) at E(n)=24 keV(approx), is used.",
                "s-wave neutron contribution to average sigma(n,g) was",
                " subtracted. The s-wave resonance parameters were used",
                " in the Bilpuch's formula.",
                " The p-wave neutron strength are then extracted from",
                " the same formula by Bilpuch et al., using the",
                " experimental values of average p-wave radiation width",
                " and level spacing."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ERR-ANALYS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "heading": "DATA-ERR",
                "minimum_value": null,
                "maximum_value": null,
                "correlation_property": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                " Combined error due to the error present in",
                " the average radiative cross-section and the errors in",
                " s- and p- wave resonance parameters."
              ]
            }
          ],
